cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark, dataset, or harness, please cite the following technical report (V12 — Second Update, 100,000-patient cohort)."
type: software
title: "Kantesti AI Engine (2.78T) — Blood Test Benchmark V12 (Second Update, 100K Cohort)"
abstract: >-
  A pre-registered, rubric-based clinical validation of the Kantesti AI Engine
  (version 2.78T) on 100,000 anonymised blood test cases drawn from a SQL-backed
  clinical data repository spanning 127 countries and 75+ languages. This V12
  release is the second update of the Kantesti Blood Test Benchmark suite,
  extending the earlier V11 proof-of-concept (15 anonymised cases) to a
  population-scale evaluation. The engine achieved a composite score of
  approximately 0.998 (99.80%) with perfect structural conformance, near-perfect
  clinical conformance, a mean end-to-end response latency of 13.26 seconds, and
  zero hyperdiagnosis false-positives on the trap-case subset. The full
  evaluation harness — including the SQL-driven case loader — is released under
  the MIT licence.
